Sentencas: This paper presents a study of mathematical modeling and steady-state analysis of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Mathematical modeling and steady-state analysis of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The SOFC has a SrCe0.95Yb0.05O3-alpha (SCY) electrolyte and two platinum electrodes.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling and steady-state analysis of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: A mathematical model of the SOFC is first developed.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling and steady-state analysis of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The model captures electrochemical processes as well as the transport phenomena.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling and steady-state analysis of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The existence of steady-state multiplicity in the cell under three modes of constant ohmic load, potentiostatic and galvanostatic operations is studied.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling and steady-state analysis of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Simulation results show that a multiple steady-states region exists at low inlet fuel and air temperatures under constant ohmic load and potentiostatic operations.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling and steady-state analysis of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The occurrence of ignition and extinction in the cell solid (electrolyte, anode and cathode) temperature is reported.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling and steady-state analysis of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This result is in agreement with those for oxygen ion-conducting solid oxide fuel cells in which the existence of steady-state multiplicity has been attributed to the dependence of the electrolyte oxygen-ion conductivity on temperature.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling and steady-state analysis of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This work shows that concentration and temperature multiplicities coexist.
Titulo: Mathematical modeling and steady-state analysis of a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell
